The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 London, March 22 (PTI): A Sikh policeman has won 9,000 in compensation for racial discrimination after British police rejected 12 transfer applications from him.          gram Singh Bhacker, 41, currently working for the British transport police, has been trying to join Greater Manchester police since 1990 to be with his family and ailing mother, who died last year. The judge said the force appeared to be deliberately evasive in its responses to questions about a race relations act questionnaire.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): A 12-year-old girl was allegedly raped by her stepfather in a central Mumbai slum on Friday. The girls mother was out when Zakir Hussain Lashkar, 37, is said to have raped her. Police have picked up Zakir for questioning.                   
	Gwalior (PTI): Eighteen cows were run over by an express train at a railway crossing near Rairu station, about 12km from here. The incident occurred when the cows were crossing the tracks with the gates open. The owner of the cows has been promised compensation.                  
	Srinagar (PTI): At least 11 children fell ill on Friday after a meal at a community kitchen where people were celebrating Id-e-Milad-un-Nabi in Anantnag district. The kids were taken to hospital where they were diagnosed with food poisoning.                                                                                                                           
